009555e963ae6723.voiceContent: Lady Malikata gave her the Khvarena to protect the rainforest, and Lord Al-Ahmar gave her the Wedjat Eye to record the moments they shared together

0b423199f53fa3c5.voiceContent: By the way, Miss Candace, I noticed you're carrying the other half of the Wedjat Eye

1b424a3662a81183.voiceContent: Uh, by bad guy... Do you mean me

2a4b10aaa736c102.voiceContent: Wait, I didn't hear anything. It's not like Hermanubis would call on you and not me..

35009b052c6aea1a.voiceContent: Little bit too much chatter from the audience over there

3e1ca8017892e80c.voiceContent: I was definitely surprised it still has the power to record events after all this time

42ac941325f80f2e.voiceContent: Despite the damage, it still holds many scenes from the past

4b8aced457698219.voiceContent: *sigh* Genius Invokation this, and Genius Invokation that... When's Collei gonna give me an excuse to leave...

5e837c71cf73c530.voiceContent: Then, you can probably guess what really happened

6a2a3b6542149627.voiceContent: You all go ahead. I'll stay here

839302a12b76edcb.voiceContent: I've never really thought about it... It's kind of like an ancient palace, in a way. Not many people are going to break off a piece of the wall and send it for appraisal..

ad00c1f89a2f5cdd.voiceContent: Its power seems to only resonate with the people of Al-Ahmar, also know as the descendants of King Deshret

b0d11391c67ebfa2.voiceContent: Legend has it that King Deshret and the Goddess of Flowers, Lady Malikata, both prepared surprise gifts for Lesser Lord Kusanali during the first Sabzeruz Festival

b0ee1c50ee70c4ec.voiceContent: Wow, can't believe we've walked this far already..

b1f9f7a370fefd74.voiceContent: That's right. So you've read the legend, too

b5a005a01df766e3.voiceContent: They've probably had enough, don't you think

c267183fdec44aba.voiceContent: Am I not supposed to be here

c469f60ae2983a37.voiceContent: If you don't mind, I'd like to place them under the custody of the Temple of Silence

c524a8061ce364a0.voiceContent: Eventually, she arrived at a lake, where she heard the sound of music. Lord Al-Ahmar was plucking the strings of an instrument while Lady Malikata performed a beautiful dance

da1d74b9e09c8554.voiceContent: You can borrow it for research, if you want

df16ea57e191e497.voiceContent: Well, that explanation starts with the first time I met Sorush

e3a6d6698ef70bb1.voiceContent: Oh, you mean this cracked Wedjat Eye

ef1908225c7ac550.voiceContent: Guess I'll stay here, then. There's a bunch of monsters nearby, so it's always good to have someone stand guard

f68e57b835c0c3cc.voiceContent: The name's Sethos. I was out for a walk when I heard the commotion, so I came to check it out

f7b843c9e042c1ee.voiceContent: The Bloomguard, Sorush — renowned among the Pari. All children of the desert know your name

06c3328450d2afae.voiceContent: If you're always asking Why?, you end up thinking yourself into a corner. Sometimes, it's better to let go

09dc9bb9ecebc8e1.voiceContent: You have to be fully prepared before you venture out on a trip, especially when you're going somewhere you haven't been before. The first time I spent the night in the rainforest, I didn't realize that I should've brought a waterproof groundsheet... That was a miserable night

0e5f90e9088f4aee.voiceContent: I'm okay, I still got this..

0f2a624ccb027360.voiceContent: Hey, check this out. See anything you like

100f1a216a1b6683.voiceContent: Green vegetables are nice to look at and all, but eating them... Ehh

15dd0843de078d98.voiceContent: I'm gonna hit the hay. Wanna catch the sunrise tomorrow

1ad1a3c128a3d4dc.voiceContent: Cyno is truly outstanding — absolutely a worthy heir to Hermanubis's power. As General Mahamatra, he has the utmost reverence for knowledge and wisdom. If the Akademiya and the Temple of Silence do start working together again, I'll take comfort in the fact that he's there.Oh yeah, and another great thing about Cyno You know the way he talks? It's just... so funny

22c12931325557f1.voiceContent: Cool cool cool, you're the boss

2bb343f1dd7a8778.voiceContent: No umbrella for me, thanks. It hardly ever rains in the desert, so I'm gonna enjoy this while I can

34ed008b43f58351.voiceContent: Do you hear that? Something's going on over there. I wanna go check it out — early bird gets the worm

364e6d38c7750e9e.voiceContent: I get bored when I'm inside for too long. I always like exploring the great outdoors, whatever the weather might be like

4357581c62a203a2.voiceContent: You got questions? You've come to the right person. On the off chance I don't have the answers, I can ask around and help you find out

44803c2e0d224174.voiceContent: I like going on hiking trips. I always map out my route, pack a bag, and pick a good day. I enjoy having it all carefully planned out. Of course, you gotta leave some flexibility in your schedule, too — you might make a new friend along the way

4fc6f2665ab2e868.voiceContent: The desert's a pretty lifeless place during the day, but you can't beat the view of the stars at night

5008e3f3f539cdcb.voiceContent: Tighnari's made of strong stuff. I only found out after the fact that he doesn't cope well with the desert climate — never would've guessed from how he performed in the Rite of Duels. I was also surprised when he sent me a letter inviting me to visit Gandharva Ville, saying it would be a good chance to meet some of Cyno's friends. Are those guys always such a hoot with their jokes? Dinner with them must be hilarious — I can't wait

52fc2db9b2fdfd0d.voiceContent: You know, your hair would look amazing if it was done up in a desert-dweller style... How about kicking off the next year of your life with a new hairdo, huh? If you're up for it, just leave it to me. You'll look glamorous, I promise you

532857cd9c311aa6.voiceContent: Have you ever experienced Candace's hospitality? She cooks very generous portions — even I could barely finish. So long as you're on the receiving end of her hospitality and not her wrath, you'll live a long and happy life

57cad5825eaf6338.voiceContent: Hmm... hmm... Nope, I can't really taste anything. Let me try some more..

6157ebac19ea0dfb.voiceContent: No no no... Quick, let's get to lower ground

62beae3d9481033e.voiceContent: Aah! It's a monster! ...No dice? I'll get you next time

666f747031f97304.voiceContent: Have you ever tried drawing in the sand? From up high, it makes for an incredible sight! But you need to pick somewhere less exposed to the wind

699a9bece030389d.voiceContent: Who is that guy, anyway? A foreign exchange student, or something? He has a pretty incredible hat, never seen anything like it. I tried to get a closer look once, but then I blinked and he was gone. Shame. I won't let him get away next time, though. I also hear he has some pretty interesting ideas... Gotta have a chat with him sometime

7b27bad5cc9ef32e.voiceContent: Mm, mm, mm! I'm kind of a big eater, hope that's okay with you

7c28ed2a2a33273f.voiceContent: Some of my elders say I'm difficult to control, like a wild animal. I actually don't disagree with that, but don't you think it's kind of an issue that they'd want to control how other people think in the first place

7ea39b80678c0213.voiceContent: Amazing... I feel like I could sprint from Aaru Village all the way to The Mausoleum of King Deshret without breaking a sweat. I'm not even joking — you up for it

7fcd8792120e000d.voiceContent: This is your training regimen, huh? Interesting

8c6fc106b39b367c.voiceContent: I usually can't stay still for more than a few minutes, but Zubayr Theater is one place I don't mind just standing and watching while Nilou dances on the stage. It's a rare skill to be able to bring people such a sense of peace

8ef85d32df73c21d.voiceContent: When desert people receive a Vision, everyone will claim it's a blessing from such-and-such a god, depending on their faith. Watching them get into an argument over someone else's Vision, about who's stronger out of Lord Hermanubis and Lord Sobek, is a guilty pleasure of mine

8f4cfa48d2b0d7f3.voiceContent: #Sorry {M#Sir}{F#Ma'am}, were you looking for me? Hello, hello, I'm Sethos. What can I do for you? ...Actually, you know what? This seems like more of a sit-down conversation. Come with me, I know a good place

983ee2ad9aa368ba.voiceContent: The weather's so perfect, it would be such a waste not to go camping. How does fishing in an oasis sound

9dc876249162e7c5.voiceContent: If you've any equipment or tools that need repairing, I can help you with that. ...What's my job? Well, I'm an unemployed vagrant, obviously. I wouldn't have the time to be such a handyman otherwise, would I

a103cf3975b53a70.voiceContent: Bags packed and ready to roll

a2224a363e9a563f.voiceContent: I always have a great time at the Grand Bazaar. I like to pick a bunch of different herbs and spices to mix with some freshly grilled meat. I never make a note of the exact combination of ingredients though, so I usually end up with one-off recipes. What do you think? Any interest in trying one of my limited-edition, one-time-only delicacies

a9d5f69954ffd052.voiceContent: I don't know where Mourning Flowers got their name, it's quite an evocative image though. Maybe somebody saw one wilting in the sunlight and thought it looked like a person hanging their head in sorrow

b32fa693875565d0.voiceContent: There's a lot of very fascinating people in the Akademiya... kinda makes me wanna go study there

b37fb6f0fd947b22.voiceContent: Goooood morning, wanna join me for breakfast? I'm gonna fix some Shawarma Wraps — I've been craving them since last night

b53b334b78923b8f.voiceContent: *shudder* ...Quick quick quick, let's pick up the pace! Jogging will warm us up

b6db3f00e512a11e.voiceContent: It's so rare to meet someone even more chummy than me! One minute I was taking a stroll near the Akademiya, the next minute she'd taken me on as a student, and was insisting on giving me a tour. She gave me a real fright, though, because she said that if I joined Haravatat, I'd get the 20-tongues language-learning package, mastery of all 100% guaranteed... I asked around, and it seems like that's just an in-joke among Akademiya students — there is no 20-language graduation requirement after all. But I don't get it... how is that funny? It's only gonna put people off studying there

be95aacde95d0d31.voiceContent: I saw those two at the tavern once. And another time at the cafe. ...Actually, I think I saw them once at the Grand Bazaar, too. The architect guy, he's always talking in a hushed tone — I guess he doesn't want people to hear, but uh... Okay, it's not like I purposely listen in, it's just... Something about those two guys hanging out together, you just can't look away

c1e50dbbd45822c0.voiceContent: I had no idea you'd help me reach this level. Sometimes, an over-reliance on ancient wisdom can make you forget the strength that you and your companions already have. Thank you for being there to remind me

ce06ef795b0a54a8.voiceContent: Lighting a bonfire at night keeps you warm and keeps wild animals away. To me, you're just like a bonfire.Too abstract? Alright, let me put it more directly I think of you as a good friend

deeaf877626907de.voiceContent: It's tempting to have a coffee at this hour, but it'll ruin your afternoon nap

e38f53c0bbf1bb54.voiceContent: Not bad! What's the recipe? I'll take some on my next hiking trip

eb5215381a4b3670.voiceContent: If you're ever traveling in the desert, journeying by night is a good choice. It does get very cold, but you don't get as dehydrated as you would under the harsh sun. Putting on a few extra layers is way easier than spending half your journey time looking for a water source

ec86a18d93ba30f1.voiceContent: To be honest, being a leader is a little stressful, especially in the Temple of Silence. But after all the years I spent with Grandfather, I'm at least clear in my own mind about the areas where I cannot compromise. After the Rite of Duels, and having been given the chance to make so many new friends, I now know the direction I want to take the Temple of Silence in from here on out. Don't worry — I won't mess it up

ee375be688002ee1.voiceContent: I like mixing spices — but only because it makes meat taste better. It's a means to an end

f452e83d46887f56.voiceContent: I've lived in the Temple of Silence for as long as I can remember, and to be honest, I've never had many of my own decisions to make. I'm still not sure if withstanding the power of Hermanubis was a blessing or a curse, but it definitely gave me a higher purpose in life.There's a million things you can regret in life, so I'm just happy I was able to bring that one situation to a close. I'm sure Grandfather will rest in peace knowing that I got to become the leader of the Temple of Silence, and that Hermanubis's power has finally found a home

f5b7531e98919f85.voiceContent: When you approach someone while intending to ingratiate yourself with them, it often makes for a stilted conversation. It's much easier to build up a rapport by just hanging out and talking about whatever

f9b76988a838420a.voiceContent: Wow... So this is what three consecutive days of reading feels like

fd7c212a9660c288.voiceContent: Flame-Mane... everyone in the desert knows that name. The Eremites aren't exactly saints, as I'm sure you know, but Dehya's one of the few solid and dependable ones out there. If you ever want to explore the Great Red Sand, Dehya's the second-best guide you could ask for. First-best being me, obviously
